The instruction asks for a formula so that if there is a middle initial present, a period is added after it, otherwise the cell stays blank. The clean literal implementation is to replace `F7` with a guarded formula based on `F10`, e.g. `=IF(TRIM(F10)="","",LEFT(F10,1)&".")`.

I should update only that cell, save to the output directory with the same filename, then reload and verify the formula was written correctly.
Code:
```repl
import os
from openpyxl import load_workbook

# Load workbook
infile = input_spreadsheet
filename = os.path.basename(infile)
outdir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet"
outfile = os.path.join(outdir, filename)

wb = load_workbook(infile)
ws = wb["Sheet1"]

# Update F7 to return middle initial with period, or blank if no middle name/initial
ws["F7"] = '=IF(TRIM(F10)="","",LEFT(F10,1)&".")'

# Save output
wb.save(outfile)

# Verify by reopening
wb_check = load_workbook(outfile, data_only=False)
ws_check = wb_check["Sheet1"]
print("Saved to:", outfile)
print("F7 formula:", ws_check["F7"].value)
print("E9 formula:", ws_check["E9"].value)
print("F10 formula:", ws_check["F10"].value)
```
